Argv parsing (via `clap`) and top-level orchestration entry for the `ctx-summarize` binary; the only place command-line invocation is translated into a `runner::run` call.

`Cli` has one subcommand, `Command::Paths { paths }`, taking an explicit list of repo-relative source paths — no glob/discovery mode exists here. Global flags: `--prompts` (default `"prompts"`) sets the prompt-file directory, and `--approve` bypasses a size guard in `runner::scope_check` that otherwise refuses runs over `MAX_TARGETS` files.

`pub fn dispatch<F: Fs, A: Agent, W: Write>(fs: &F, agent: &A, cli: &Cli, out: &mut W) -> Result<(), SummError>` is the sole entry point: it checks scope, calls `runner::run`, then serializes the resulting summary as pretty JSON to `out` followed by a trailing newline. JSON write errors are wrapped as `SummError::Io` with path `"<stdout>"` — not the real output destination, so error messages here are synthetic. Depends on `runner::run`'s summary type being `Serialize`-compatible; changing that type's shape changes the emitted JSON without any check in this file.